  {
    q: "My rotisserie motor died. Worth repairing on a year-10 grill?",
    a: "Honest answer: usually skip the repair. Rotisserie motor is luxury accessory, not cooking-critical. The grill works perfectly without it. $260 to $440 motor replacement on a year 10+ unit makes sense if you use the rotisserie monthly; doesn't make sense if you've used it twice. Most owners stop using rotisserie after the first failure and don't miss it. We'll tell you straight at $120 dx whether your usage justifies the repair."
