<!-- 06 MARINE LAYER ANGLE -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">06 · LA marine layer corrosion pattern</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">200+ humidity nights per year on coastal installations.</h2>

    <p>Marine layer is the most underappreciated factor in coastal grill electrical lifespans. Condensation cycles night after night in the built-in cabinet enclosure infiltrate junction terminations, control panel circuit boards, and LED ribbon connectors. Salt-air variant of marine layer (within 1 mile of ocean) doubles the rate again because chloride ions accelerate copper oxidation.</p>

    <p>Failure rate by location:</p>
    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li><strong>Within 1 mile of ocean (Malibu, Newport Coast, Manhattan Beach Strand, Laguna PCH):</strong> control panels fail year 5 to 7, junction boxes year 6 to 8, LED ribbons year 4 to 7.</li>
      <li><strong>1 to 5 miles inland (Pacific Palisades, Hermosa, Newport inland, Laguna Niguel):</strong> control panels year 7 to 10, junction boxes year 8 to 10, LED ribbons year 6 to 9.</li>
      <li><strong>5+ miles inland (Beverly Hills, West Hollywood, Encino, Calabasas, Irvine inland):</strong> control panels year 10+, junction boxes year 10+, LED ribbons year 8 to 12.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>Preventive marine-grade re-termination service ($180 to $260) at year 5 on coastal grills extends junction box service life 4 to 7 years. We schedule it for clients on annual coastal maintenance.</p>
  </div>
</section>

